150
00:07:53,017 --> 00:07:54,277
based on what Metacritic says.

151
00:07:55,377 --> 00:07:58,338
And that's how the sales chart looked during release.

152
00:07:58,578 --> 00:08:00,418
I don't have to point out where the game came out.

153
00:08:00,818 --> 00:08:01,619
It was very obvious.

154
00:08:02,219 --> 00:08:03,899
But even though the game was doing quite well,

155
00:08:04,279 --> 00:08:06,839
I wasn't happy because the game was kind of rushed

156
00:08:07,480 --> 00:08:10,280
and it still lacked in certain aspects.

157
00:08:10,320 --> 00:08:13,921
So I had these four pillars that I wanted to fix about the game,

158
00:08:14,001 --> 00:08:15,041
which was content,

159
00:08:15,575 --> 00:08:18,336
replay value, online gameplay, and marketing.

160
00:08:19,156 --> 00:08:21,017
And so the updates era started.

161
00:08:21,597 --> 00:08:24,118
And I wanted to maintain the game with updates

162
00:08:24,458 --> 00:08:27,739
with the no paid DLC mentality.

163
00:08:28,319 --> 00:08:29,939
And I wanted to really stick to that.

164
00:08:30,059 --> 00:08:34,000
So back then, I was looking at what Team Fortress was doing.

165
00:08:34,220 --> 00:08:35,901
And they had these very cool updates

166
00:08:36,061 --> 00:08:39,762
that had their own logo, their own website, a tiny trailer.

167
00:08:39,882 --> 00:08:41,782
And all the features were presented super nicely

168
00:08:41,922 --> 00:08:42,583
on that website.

169
00:08:43,363 --> 00:08:43,483
So.

170
00:08:43,919 --> 00:08:46,141
We started working on the first update, which

171
00:08:46,201 --> 00:08:49,083
was focused on fixing the replay value problems of the game.

172
00:08:49,583 --> 00:08:52,405
And so the Mutators update was released in March.

173
00:08:52,805 --> 00:08:56,108
And the Mutators update was all about adding

174
00:08:56,368 --> 00:08:59,870
mutators that add new mechanics to the game as you're playing.

175
00:09:00,531 --> 00:09:03,373
And the game was kind of getting popular

176
00:09:03,473 --> 00:09:04,674
with YouTubers back then.

